Rating: 3
This was my first gumbo attempt and I'm really happy with the way it came out! I'd give more stars but like other reviewers, didn't follow the recipe as written. I did a lot of roux research and after reading reviews I had planned to follow the 1:1 ratio of flour and butter but accidentally only did two sticks of butter instead of four and didn't realize it until the end. [Whoops!] I cooked the roux over low heat for an hour stirring very frequently until it was a dark copper color. Even with that mistake, my gumbo still came out great! I didn't have much fat to skim off either. Adjustments I made: sauteed the vegetables ahead of time, reduced broth to four cartons, used 1 tbsp less of cajun seasoning and salt, added raw Louisiana shrimp, used a rotisserie chicken from the grocery, and grilled my sausage before adding. Will make again!!

