I am not partial to chicken gumbo. I lived in Southern Louisiana as a pre teen and teen ager. Where ever the oil drilling rigs were, thats where I was. I spent one summer living with a Cajun family on Bayou du Portage between New Iberia and Breaux Bridge. The mother taught me how to cook. In her opinion, if it wasn't seafood gumbo, it wasn't gumbo. Most of the people in Southern Louisiana seemed to feel the same way. Things have gotten easier now -- It is a lot easier to use Tony Chachere's Creole Seasoning than mixing up a batch - comes out better too. Make a good dark roux and use a lot of shrimp, craw fish, oysters, cat fish, crabs (messy but good) and any other seafood available. Kitchen Bouquet also helps with the taste and color, too. Use good fresh Gumbo File for flavor and thickening. It needs to be served over some good rice.

