Rating: 4
As a chef from western Pa. I couldn't help but notice an important step left out of this otherwise great recipe. Then, upon reading the reviews for it and seeing that almost everyone experienced the problem, I felt that I must clue future users of this recipe into the step. Most reviews complained of a overly floury taste, this is due to the fact that the flour products are not skimmed off. You see, when using a roux as a thickening agent, one must "skim the scum" off as it simmers. After adding the liquid and bringing it up to temperture, reduce heat to a slow simmer, allow it to sit without stirring, a scum will form, this is comprised of mostly flour, skim this off and repeat process several times, this will remove the floury taste to the recipe. It is important to not stir this "scum" back into the dish.

