Rating: 4
Overall this is a fantastic recipe for Gumbo. It is REALLY important to fix the roux ratios however. You should start with a 1:1 ratio, 2c flour to 2c (4sticks) butter. And definitely let the roux get really dark, it does wonders for the flavor. I added Okra and made my own chicken stock by boiling the leftover chicken with all of the leftover vegetable remains. I think that made a big difference. Also - I found these INCREDIBLE "oven-smoker" bags at a grocery store in Manhattan. It is a tin-foil bag that you put your chicken in, then bake in the oven. Adds an fabulous & authentic smoked chicken flavor to the gumbo. Also, next time I make this Gumbo I will use more chicken.

