Rating: 4
Contrary to the first reviewer, the original recipe from Mr. G's Bistro website calls for 1 pound of butter to 1 pound of flour. A pound of flour is roughly 3 cups, so I made the roux with 2c butter to 3c flour. Many other roux recipes I've seen support this 2 to 3 ratio. It was perfect! I think 2 to 2 would have been too thin.

