This was my first attempt at a roux. After burning the first one, I was ready to completely discard this recipe out of sheer frustration. (i'd already worked about 45 minutes!) Thank god I didn't! Who knew heaven came in a bowl?!? So yummy...tastes just like some I had a jazz fest this year in new orleans.

Rating: 3
I should have printed all reviews before starting! The Roux was indeed thick as everyone else mentioned, and took more than the suggested hour. It was tasty and appealing the first day, but didn't reheat that well. It congealed easily, but did not affect the taste. I'll definitely decrease the flour if I make it again.

Rating: 3
This was excellent!I took the advice of other reviewers and cut the flour by 2C (a mahogany roux can also be made with oil and flour over med-high heat constantly stirred in about 5 minutes, for those of you in a hurry). I added 8 diced roma tomatoes, 1.5 lbs. sliced fresh okra, and 1.5 lbs. rock shrimp. This is my new recipe for gumbo. YUMMOLIA!!!!

Rating: 4
Time-consuming to make, but well worth the effort! Received raves from all who were lucky enough to try a sample. Took the advice of other reviewers and cut the roux to 2c butter and 2c flour. Excellent!

