Rating: 4
I started out with the same problem as nan, but luckily was able to salvage by adding another stick of butter (to half batch). I think the butter to flour ratio is incorrect: should be 2c flour to 4 sticks of butter. The given proportions makes a dough, not a roux. Turned out very delicious!

Rating: 3
Did anyone else have problems with the roux? I made half a recipe and ended up with concrete for the roux. Added up to 1 qt of chicken stock to try and salvage the situation, but to no avail. So I started over with a basic roux of 1/3 C olive oil and 1/4 cup plus 2 TBS of flour. Great roux, but the gumbo didn't thicken--probably because there wasn't any okra. Any suggestions? The final dish was tasty, but needed a lot of rice and file to thicken.

